# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1884-detroit-wolverines-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1881-detroit-wolverines-season] Thompson bought most of the players from the defunct Cincinnati Reds franchise and formed the **Detroit Wolverines**, which joined the National League.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1881-detroit-wolverines-season] The team finished the season with a 41–43 record, good enough for fourth place in the NL race.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1882-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1882 Detroit Wolverines** finished the season with a 42–41 record, good for fifth place in the National League.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1882-detroit-wolverines-season] During the season, Detroit owner William G.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1882-detroit-wolverines-season] Thompson had a private investigator look into umpire Richard Higham, after suspicions of matchfixing, which resulted in Higham becoming the only umpire to be banned in MLB history.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1883-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1883 Detroit Wolverines** finished the season with a 40–58 record, good for seventh place in the National League.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1884-baltimore-monumentals-season] The **1884 Baltimore Monumentals** finished with a 58–47 record in the Union Association, finishing in fourth place.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1884-baltimore-monumentals-season] This was the only season this version of the team existed, and indeed the only season the Union Association existed.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1884-boston-beaneaters-season] The **1884 Boston Beaneaters season** was the 14th season of the franchise.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1884-boston-reds-season] The **1884 Boston Reds** finished with a 58–51 record in the Union Association, finishing in fifth place (fourth among teams that played a full schedule).
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1884-boston-reds-season] This was the only season the team existed, and indeed the only season the Union Association existed.
[src:1884-detroit-wolverines-season/1884-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1884 Detroit Wolverines** finished the season with a 28–84 record, finishing in last place in the National League.
